196static bool qt_detectRTLLanguage()
197{
198 return force_reverse ^
199 (QGuiApplication::tr(s: "QT_LAYOUT_DIRECTION",
200 c: "Translate this string to the string 'LTR' in left-to-right"
201 " languages or to 'RTL' in right-to-left languages (such as Hebrew"
202 " and Arabic) to get proper widget layout.") == "RTL"_L1);
203}

205static void initFontUnlocked()
206{
207 if (!QGuiApplicationPrivate::app_font) {
208 if (const QPlatformTheme *theme = QGuiApplicationPrivate::platformTheme())
209 if (const QFont *font = theme->font(type: QPlatformTheme::SystemFont))
210 QGuiApplicationPrivate::app_font = new QFont(*font);
211 }
212 if (!QGuiApplicationPrivate::app_font)
213 QGuiApplicationPrivate::app_font =
214 new QFont(QGuiApplicationPrivate::platformIntegration()->fontDatabase()->defaultFont());
215}
216
217static inline void clearFontUnlocked()
218{
219 delete QGuiApplicationPrivate::app_font;
220 QGuiApplicationPrivate::app_font = nullptr;
221}

238// Using aggregate initialization instead of ctor so we can have a POD global static
239#define Q_WINDOW_GEOMETRY_SPECIFICATION_INITIALIZER { Qt::TopLeftCorner, -1, -1, -1, -1 }
240
241// Geometry specification for top level windows following the convention of the
242// -geometry command line arguments in X11 (see XParseGeometry).
243struct QWindowGeometrySpecification
244{
245 static QWindowGeometrySpecification fromArgument(const QByteArray &a);
246 void applyTo(QWindow *window) const;
247
248 Qt::Corner corner;
249 int xOffset;
250 int yOffset;
251 int width;
252 int height;
253};
254
255// Parse a token of a X11 geometry specification "200x100+10-20".
256static inline int nextGeometryToken(const QByteArray &a, int &pos, char *op)
257{
258 *op = 0;
259 const int size = a.size();
260 if (pos >= size)
261 return -1;
262
263 *op = a.at(i: pos);
264 if (*op == '+' || *op == '-' || *op == 'x')
265 pos++;
266 else if (isdigit(*op))
267 *op = 'x'; // If it starts with a digit, it is supposed to be a width specification.
268 else
269 return -1;
270
271 const int numberPos = pos;
272 for ( ; pos < size && isdigit(a.at(i: pos)); ++pos) ;
273
274 bool ok;
275 const int result = a.mid(index: numberPos, len: pos - numberPos).toInt(ok: &ok);
276 return ok ? result : -1;
277}
278
279QWindowGeometrySpecification QWindowGeometrySpecification::fromArgument(const QByteArray &a)
280{
281 QWindowGeometrySpecification result = Q_WINDOW_GEOMETRY_SPECIFICATION_INITIALIZER;
282 int pos = 0;
283 for (int i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
284 char op;
285 const int value = nextGeometryToken(a, pos, op: &op);
286 if (value < 0)
287 break;
288 switch (op) {
289 case 'x':
290 (result.width >= 0 ? result.height : result.width) = value;
291 break;
292 case '+':
293 case '-':
294 if (result.xOffset >= 0) {
295 result.yOffset = value;
296 if (op == '-')
297 result.corner = result.corner == Qt::TopRightCorner ? Qt::BottomRightCorner : Qt::BottomLeftCorner;
298 } else {
299 result.xOffset = value;
300 if (op == '-')
301 result.corner = Qt::TopRightCorner;
302 }
303 }
304 }
305 return result;
306}
307
308void QWindowGeometrySpecification::applyTo(QWindow *window) const
309{
310 QRect windowGeometry = window->frameGeometry();
311 QSize size = windowGeometry.size();
312 if (width >= 0 || height >= 0) {
313 const QSize windowMinimumSize = window->minimumSize();
314 const QSize windowMaximumSize = window->maximumSize();
315 if (width >= 0)
316 size.setWidth(qBound(min: windowMinimumSize.width(), val: width, max: windowMaximumSize.width()));
317 if (height >= 0)
318 size.setHeight(qBound(min: windowMinimumSize.height(), val: height, max: windowMaximumSize.height()));
319 window->resize(newSize: size);
320 }
321 if (xOffset >= 0 || yOffset >= 0) {
322 const QRect availableGeometry = window->screen()->virtualGeometry();
323 QPoint topLeft = windowGeometry.topLeft();
324 if (xOffset >= 0) {
325 topLeft.setX(corner == Qt::TopLeftCorner || corner == Qt::BottomLeftCorner ?
326 xOffset :
327 qMax(a: availableGeometry.right() - size.width() - xOffset, b: availableGeometry.left()));
328 }
329 if (yOffset >= 0) {
330 topLeft.setY(corner == Qt::TopLeftCorner || corner == Qt::TopRightCorner ?
331 yOffset :
332 qMax(a: availableGeometry.bottom() - size.height() - yOffset, b: availableGeometry.top()));
333 }
334 window->setFramePosition(topLeft);
335 }
336}

341 \macro qGuiApp

345 Only valid for use when that object is a QGuiApplication.

350/*!
351 \class QGuiApplication
352 \brief The QGuiApplication class manages the GUI application's control
353 flow and main settings.
354
355 \inmodule QtGui
356 \since 5.0
357
358 QGuiApplication contains the main event loop, where all events from the window
359 system and other sources are processed and dispatched. It also handles the
360 application's initialization and finalization, and provides session management.
361 In addition, QGuiApplication handles most of the system-wide and application-wide
362 settings.
363
364 For any GUI application using Qt, there is precisely \b one QGuiApplication
365 object no matter whether the application has 0, 1, 2 or more windows at
366 any given time. For non-GUI Qt applications, use QCoreApplication instead,
367 as it does not depend on the Qt GUI module. For QWidget based Qt applications,
368 use QApplication instead, as it provides some functionality needed for creating
369 QWidget instances.
370
371 The QGuiApplication object is accessible through the instance() function, which
372 returns a pointer equivalent to the global \l qApp pointer.
373
374 QGuiApplication's main areas of responsibility are:
375 \list
376 \li It initializes the application with the user's desktop settings,
377 such as palette(), font() and styleHints(). It keeps
378 track of these properties in case the user changes the desktop
379 globally, for example, through some kind of control panel.
380
381 \li It performs event handling, meaning that it receives events
382 from the underlying window system and dispatches them to the
383 relevant widgets. You can send your own events to windows by
384 using sendEvent() and postEvent().
385
386 \li It parses common command line arguments and sets its internal
387 state accordingly. See the \l{QGuiApplication::QGuiApplication()}
388 {constructor documentation} below for more details.
389
390 \li It provides localization of strings that are visible to the
391 user via translate().
392
393 \li It provides some magical objects like the clipboard().
394
395 \li It knows about the application's windows. You can ask which
396 window is at a certain position using topLevelAt(), get a list of
397 topLevelWindows(), etc.
398
399 \li It manages the application's mouse cursor handling, see
400 setOverrideCursor()
401
402 \li It provides support for sophisticated \l{Session Management}
403 {session management}. This makes it possible for applications
404 to terminate gracefully when the user logs out, to cancel a
405 shutdown process if termination isn't possible and even to
406 preserve the entire application's state for a future session.
407 See isSessionRestored(), sessionId() and commitDataRequest() and
408 saveStateRequest() for details.
409 \endlist
410
411 Since the QGuiApplication object does so much initialization, it \e{must} be
412 created before any other objects related to the user interface are created.
413 QGuiApplication also deals with common command line arguments. Hence, it is
414 usually a good idea to create it \e before any interpretation or
415 modification of \c argv is done in the application itself.
416
417 \table
418 \header
419 \li{2,1} Groups of functions
420
421 \row
422 \li System settings
423 \li desktopSettingsAware(),
424 setDesktopSettingsAware(),
425 styleHints(),
426 palette(),
427 setPalette(),
428 font(),
429 setFont().
430
431 \row
432 \li Event handling
433 \li exec(),
434 processEvents(),
435 exit(),
436 quit().
437 sendEvent(),
438 postEvent(),
439 sendPostedEvents(),
440 removePostedEvents(),
441 notify().
442
443 \row
444 \li Windows
445 \li allWindows(),
446 topLevelWindows(),
447 focusWindow(),
448 clipboard(),
449 topLevelAt().
450
451 \row
452 \li Advanced cursor handling
453 \li overrideCursor(),
454 setOverrideCursor(),
455 restoreOverrideCursor().
456
457 \row
458 \li Session management
459 \li isSessionRestored(),
460 sessionId(),
461 commitDataRequest(),
462 saveStateRequest().
463
464 \row
465 \li Miscellaneous
466 \li startingUp(),
467 closingDown().
468 \endtable
469
470 \sa QCoreApplication, QAbstractEventDispatcher, QEventLoop
471*/
472
473/*!
474 Initializes the window system and constructs an application object with
475 \a argc command line arguments in \a argv.
476
477 \warning The data referred to by \a argc and \a argv must stay valid for
478 the entire lifetime of the QGuiApplication object. In addition, \a argc must
479 be greater than zero and \a argv must contain at least one valid character
480 string.
481
482 The global \c qApp pointer refers to this application object. Only one
483 application object should be created.
484
485 This application object must be constructed before any \l{QPaintDevice}
486 {paint devices} (including pixmaps, bitmaps etc.).
487
488 \note \a argc and \a argv might be changed as Qt removes command line
489 arguments that it recognizes.
490
491 \section1 Supported Command Line Options
492
493 All Qt programs automatically support a set of command-line options that
494 allow modifying the way Qt will interact with the windowing system. Some of
495 the options are also accessible via environment variables, which are the
496 preferred form if the application can launch GUI sub-processes or other
497 applications (environment variables will be inherited by child processes).
498 When in doubt, use the environment variables.
499
500 The options currently supported are the following:
501 \list
502
503 \li \c{-platform} \e {platformName[:options]}, specifies the
504 \l{Qt Platform Abstraction} (QPA) plugin.
505
506 Overrides the \c QT_QPA_PLATFORM environment variable.
507 \li \c{-platformpluginpath} \e path, specifies the path to platform
508 plugins.
509
510 Overrides the \c QT_QPA_PLATFORM_PLUGIN_PATH environment variable.
511
512 \li \c{-platformtheme} \e platformTheme, specifies the platform theme.
513
514 Overrides the \c QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME environment variable.
515
516 \li \c{-plugin} \e plugin, specifies additional plugins to load. The argument
517 may appear multiple times.
518
519 Concatenated with the plugins in the \c QT_QPA_GENERIC_PLUGINS environment
520 variable.
521
522 \li \c{-qmljsdebugger=}, activates the QML/JS debugger with a specified port.
523 The value must be of format \c{port:1234}\e{[,block]}, where
524 \e block is optional
525 and will make the application wait until a debugger connects to it.
526 \li \c {-qwindowgeometry} \e geometry, specifies window geometry for
527 the main window using the X11-syntax. For example:
528 \c {-qwindowgeometry 100x100+50+50}
529 \li \c {-qwindowicon}, sets the default window icon
530 \li \c {-qwindowtitle}, sets the title of the first window
531 \li \c{-reverse}, sets the application's layout direction to
532 Qt::RightToLeft. This option is intended to aid debugging and should
533 not be used in production. The default value is automatically detected
534 from the user's locale (see also QLocale::textDirection()).
535 \li \c{-session} \e session, restores the application from an earlier
536 \l{Session Management}{session}.
537 \endlist
538
539 The following standard command line options are available for X11:
540
541 \list
542 \li \c {-display} \e {hostname:screen_number}, switches displays on X11.
543
544 Overrides the \c DISPLAY environment variable.
545 \li \c {-geometry} \e geometry, same as \c {-qwindowgeometry}.
546 \endlist
547
548 \section1 Platform-Specific Arguments
549
550 You can specify platform-specific arguments for the \c{-platform} option.
551 Place them after the platform plugin name following a colon as a
552 comma-separated list. For example,
553 \c{-platform windows:dialogs=xp,fontengine=freetype}.
554
555 The following parameters are available for \c {-platform windows}:
556
557 \list
558 \li \c {altgr}, detect the key \c {AltGr} found on some keyboards as
559 Qt::GroupSwitchModifier (since Qt 5.12).
560 \li \c {darkmode=[1|2]} controls how Qt responds to the activation
561 of the \e{Dark Mode for applications} introduced in Windows 10
562 1903 (since Qt 5.15).
563
564 A value of 1 causes Qt to switch the window borders to black
565 when \e{Dark Mode for applications} is activated and no High
566 Contrast Theme is in use. This is intended for applications
567 that implement their own theming.
568
569 A value of 2 will in addition cause the Windows Vista style to
570 be deactivated and switch to the Windows style using a
571 simplified palette in dark mode. This is currently
572 experimental pending the introduction of new style that
573 properly adapts to dark mode.
574
575 As of Qt 6.5, the default value is 2; to disable dark mode
576 support, set the value to 0 or 1.
577
578 \li \c {dialogs=[xp|none]}, \c xp uses XP-style native dialogs and
579 \c none disables them.
580
581 \li \c {fontengine=freetype}, uses the FreeType font engine.
582 \li \c {fontengine=directwrite}, uses the experimental DirectWrite
583 font database and defaults to using the DirectWrite font
584 engine (which is otherwise only used for some font types
585 or font properties.) This affects font selection and aims
586 to provide font naming more consistent with other platforms,
587 but does not support all font formats, such as Postscript
588 Type-1 or Microsoft FNT fonts.
589 \li \c {menus=[native|none]}, controls the use of native menus.
590
591 Native menus are implemented using Win32 API and are simpler than
592 QMenu-based menus in for example that they do allow for placing
593 widgets on them or changing properties like fonts and do not
594 provide hover signals. They are mainly intended for Qt Quick.
595 By default, they will be used if the application is not an
596 instance of QApplication or for Qt Quick Controls 2
597 applications (since Qt 5.10).
598
599 \li \c {nocolorfonts} Turn off DirectWrite Color fonts
600 (since Qt 5.8).
601
602 \li \c {nodirectwrite} Turn off DirectWrite fonts (since Qt 5.8).
603
604 \li \c {nomousefromtouch} Ignores mouse events synthesized
605 from touch events by the operating system.
606
607 \li \c {nowmpointer} Switches from Pointer Input Messages handling
608 to legacy mouse handling (since Qt 5.12).
609 \li \c {reverse} Activates Right-to-left mode (experimental).
610 Windows title bars will be shown accordingly in Right-to-left locales
611 (since Qt 5.13).
612 \li \c {tabletabsoluterange=<value>} Sets a value for mouse mode detection
613 of WinTab tablets (Legacy, since Qt 5.3).
614 \endlist
615
616 The following parameter is available for \c {-platform cocoa} (on macOS):
617
618 \list
619 \li \c {fontengine=freetype}, uses the FreeType font engine.
620 \endlist
621
622 For more information about the platform-specific arguments available for
623 embedded Linux platforms, see \l{Qt for Embedded Linux}.
624
625 \sa arguments() QGuiApplication::platformName
626*/
627#ifdef Q_QDOC

629#else
630QGuiApplication::QGuiApplication(int &argc, char **argv, int)
631#endif
632 : QCoreApplication(*new QGuiApplicationPrivate(argc, argv))

634 d_func()->init();
635
636 QCoreApplicationPrivate::eventDispatcher->startingUp();
637}

647/*!
648 Destructs the application.
649*/
650QGuiApplication::~QGuiApplication()
651{
652 Q_D(QGuiApplication);
653
654 qt_call_post_routines();
655
656 d->eventDispatcher->closingDown();
657 d->eventDispatcher = nullptr;
658
659#ifndef QT_NO_CLIPBOARD
660 delete QGuiApplicationPrivate::qt_clipboard;
661 QGuiApplicationPrivate::qt_clipboard = nullptr;
662#endif
663
664#ifndef QT_NO_SESSIONMANAGER
665 delete d->session_manager;
666 d->session_manager = nullptr;
667#endif //QT_NO_SESSIONMANAGER
668
669 QGuiApplicationPrivate::clearPalette();
670 QFontDatabase::removeAllApplicationFonts();
671
672#ifndef QT_NO_CURSOR
673 d->cursor_list.clear();
674#endif
675
676 delete QGuiApplicationPrivate::app_icon;
677 QGuiApplicationPrivate::app_icon = nullptr;
678 delete QGuiApplicationPrivate::platform_name;
679 QGuiApplicationPrivate::platform_name = nullptr;
680 delete QGuiApplicationPrivate::displayName;
681 QGuiApplicationPrivate::displayName = nullptr;
682 delete QGuiApplicationPrivate::m_inputDeviceManager;
683 QGuiApplicationPrivate::m_inputDeviceManager = nullptr;
684 delete QGuiApplicationPrivate::desktopFileName;
685 QGuiApplicationPrivate::desktopFileName = nullptr;
686 QGuiApplicationPrivate::mouse_buttons = Qt::NoButton;
687 QGuiApplicationPrivate::modifier_buttons = Qt::NoModifier;
688 QGuiApplicationPrivate::lastCursorPosition.reset();
689 QGuiApplicationPrivate::currentMousePressWindow = QGuiApplicationPrivate::currentMouseWindow = nullptr;
690 QGuiApplicationPrivate::applicationState = Qt::ApplicationInactive;
691 QGuiApplicationPrivate::highDpiScaleFactorRoundingPolicy = Qt::HighDpiScaleFactorRoundingPolicy::PassThrough;
692 QGuiApplicationPrivate::currentDragWindow = nullptr;
693 QGuiApplicationPrivate::tabletDevicePoints.clear();
694}

696QGuiApplicationPrivate::QGuiApplicationPrivate(int &argc, char **argv)
697 : QCoreApplicationPrivate(argc, argv),
698 inputMethod(nullptr),

796/*!
797 Returns the most recently shown modal window. If no modal windows are
798 visible, this function returns zero.
799
800 A modal window is a window which has its
801 \l{QWindow::modality}{modality} property set to Qt::WindowModal
802 or Qt::ApplicationModal. A modal window must be closed before the user can
803 continue with other parts of the program.
804
805 Modal window are organized in a stack. This function returns the modal
806 window at the top of the stack.
807
808 \sa Qt::WindowModality, QWindow::setModality()
809*/
810QWindow *QGuiApplication::modalWindow()
811{
812 CHECK_QAPP_INSTANCE(nullptr)
813 if (QGuiApplicationPrivate::self->modalWindowList.isEmpty())
814 return nullptr;
815 return QGuiApplicationPrivate::self->modalWindowList.first();
816}
817
818static void updateBlockedStatusRecursion(QWindow *window, bool shouldBeBlocked)
819{
820 QWindowPrivate *p = qt_window_private(window);
821 if (p->blockedByModalWindow != shouldBeBlocked) {
822 p->blockedByModalWindow = shouldBeBlocked;
823 QEvent e(shouldBeBlocked ? QEvent::WindowBlocked : QEvent::WindowUnblocked);
824 QGuiApplication::sendEvent(receiver: window, event: &e);
825 for (QObject *c : window->children()) {
826 if (c->isWindowType())
827 updateBlockedStatusRecursion(window: static_cast<QWindow *>(c), shouldBeBlocked);
828 }
829 }
830}
831
832void QGuiApplicationPrivate::updateBlockedStatus(QWindow *window)
833{
834 bool shouldBeBlocked = false;
835 const bool popupType = (window->type() == Qt::ToolTip) || (window->type() == Qt::Popup);
836 if (!popupType && !self->modalWindowList.isEmpty())
837 shouldBeBlocked = self->isWindowBlocked(window);
838 updateBlockedStatusRecursion(window, shouldBeBlocked);
839}
840
841// Return whether the window needs to be notified about window blocked events.
842// As opposed to QGuiApplication::topLevelWindows(), embedded windows are
843// included in this list (QTBUG-18099).
844static inline bool needsWindowBlockedEvent(const QWindow *w)
845{
846 return w->isTopLevel() && w->type() != Qt::Desktop;
847}
848
849void QGuiApplicationPrivate::showModalWindow(QWindow *modal)
850{
851 self->modalWindowList.prepend(t: modal);
852
853 // Send leave for currently entered window if it should be blocked
854 if (currentMouseWindow && !QWindowPrivate::get(window: currentMouseWindow)->isPopup()) {
855 bool shouldBeBlocked = self->isWindowBlocked(window: currentMouseWindow);
856 if (shouldBeBlocked) {
857 // Remove the new window from modalWindowList temporarily so leave can go through
858 self->modalWindowList.removeFirst();
859 QEvent e(QEvent::Leave);
860 QGuiApplication::sendEvent(receiver: currentMouseWindow, event: &e);
861 currentMouseWindow = nullptr;
862 self->modalWindowList.prepend(t: modal);
863 }
864 }
865
866 for (QWindow *window : std::as_const(t&: QGuiApplicationPrivate::window_list)) {
867 if (needsWindowBlockedEvent(w: window) && !window->d_func()->blockedByModalWindow)
868 updateBlockedStatus(window);
869 }
870
871 updateBlockedStatus(window: modal);
872}
873
874void QGuiApplicationPrivate::hideModalWindow(QWindow *window)
875{
876 self->modalWindowList.removeAll(t: window);
877
878 for (QWindow *window : std::as_const(t&: QGuiApplicationPrivate::window_list)) {
879 if (needsWindowBlockedEvent(w: window) && window->d_func()->blockedByModalWindow)
880 updateBlockedStatus(window);
881 }
882}

884Qt::WindowModality QGuiApplicationPrivate::defaultModality() const

886 return Qt::NonModal;
887}
888
889bool QGuiApplicationPrivate::windowNeverBlocked(QWindow *window) const
890{
891 Q_UNUSED(window);
892 return false;
893}
894
895/*
896 Returns \c true if \a window is blocked by a modal window. If \a
897 blockingWindow is non-zero, *blockingWindow will be set to the blocking
898 window (or to zero if \a window is not blocked).
899*/
900bool QGuiApplicationPrivate::isWindowBlocked(QWindow *window, QWindow **blockingWindow) const
901{
902 Q_ASSERT_X(window, Q_FUNC_INFO, "The window must not be null");
903
904 QWindow *unused = nullptr;
905 if (!blockingWindow)
906 blockingWindow = &unused;
907 *blockingWindow = nullptr;
908
909 if (modalWindowList.isEmpty() || windowNeverBlocked(window))
910 return false;
911
912 for (int i = 0; i < modalWindowList.size(); ++i) {
913 QWindow *modalWindow = modalWindowList.at(i);
914
915 // A window is not blocked by another modal window if the two are
916 // the same, or if the window is a child of the modal window.
917 if (window == modalWindow || modalWindow->isAncestorOf(child: window, mode: QWindow::IncludeTransients))
918 return false;
919
920 switch (modalWindow->modality() == Qt::NonModal ? defaultModality()
921 : modalWindow->modality()) {
922 case Qt::ApplicationModal:
923 *blockingWindow = modalWindow;
924 return true;
925 case Qt::WindowModal: {
926 // Find the nearest ancestor of window which is also an ancestor of modal window to
927 // determine if the modal window blocks the window.
928 auto *current = window;
929 do {
930 if (current->isAncestorOf(child: modalWindow, mode: QWindow::IncludeTransients)) {
931 *blockingWindow = modalWindow;
932 return true;
933 }
934 current = current->parent(mode: QWindow::IncludeTransients);
935 } while (current);
936 break;
937 }
938 default:
939 Q_ASSERT_X(false, "QGuiApplication", "internal error, a modal widget cannot be modeless");
940 break;
941 }
942 }
943 return false;
944}

998/*!
999 \fn QGuiApplication::topLevelWindows()
1000
1001 Returns a list of the top-level windows in the application.
1002
1003 \sa allWindows()
1004 */
1005QWindowList QGuiApplication::topLevelWindows()
1006{
1007 const QWindowList &list = QGuiApplicationPrivate::window_list;
1008 QWindowList topLevelWindows;
1009 for (int i = 0; i < list.size(); ++i) {
1010 QWindow *window = list.at(i);
1011 if (!window->isTopLevel())
1012 continue;
1013
1014 // Desktop windows are special, as each individual desktop window
1015 // will report that it's a top level window, but we don't want to
1016 // include them in the application wide list of top level windows.
1017 if (window->type() == Qt::Desktop)
1018 continue;
1019
1020 // Windows embedded in native windows do not have QWindow parents,
1021 // but they are not true top level windows, so do not include them.
1022 if (window->handle() && window->handle()->isEmbedded())
1023 continue;
1024
1025 topLevelWindows.prepend(t: window);
1026 }
1027
1028 return topLevelWindows;
1029}

1047/*!
1048 Returns the screen at \a point, or \nullptr if outside of any screen.
1049
1050 The \a point is in relation to the virtualGeometry() of each set of virtual
1051 siblings. If the point maps to more than one set of virtual siblings the first
1052 match is returned. If you wish to search only the virtual desktop siblings
1053 of a known screen (for example siblings of the screen of your application
1054 window \c QWidget::windowHandle()->screen()), use QScreen::virtualSiblingAt().
1055
1056 \since 5.10
1057*/
1058QScreen *QGuiApplication::screenAt(const QPoint &point)
1059{
1060 QVarLengthArray<const QScreen *, 8> visitedScreens;
1061 for (const QScreen *screen : QGuiApplication::screens()) {
1062 if (visitedScreens.contains(t: screen))
1063 continue;
1064
1065 // The virtual siblings include the screen itself, so iterate directly
1066 for (QScreen *sibling : screen->virtualSiblings()) {
1067 if (sibling->geometry().contains(p: point))
1068 return sibling;
1069
1070 visitedScreens.append(t: sibling);
1071 }
1072 }
1073
1074 return nullptr;
1075}

1187
1188Q_LOGGING_CATEGORY(lcQpaPluginLoading, "qt.qpa.plugin");
1189Q_LOGGING_CATEGORY(lcQpaTheme, "qt.qpa.theme");
1190Q_LOGGING_CATEGORY(lcPtrDispatch, "qt.pointer.dispatch");
1191
1192static void init_platform(const QString &pluginNamesWithArguments, const QString &platformPluginPath, const QString &platformThemeName, int &argc, char **argv)
1193{
1194 qCDebug(lcQpaPluginLoading) << "init_platform called with"
1195 << "pluginNamesWithArguments" << pluginNamesWithArguments
1196 << "platformPluginPath" << platformPluginPath
1197 << "platformThemeName" << platformThemeName;
1198
1199 QStringList plugins = pluginNamesWithArguments.split(sep: u';', behavior: Qt::SkipEmptyParts);
1200 QStringList platformArguments;
1201 QStringList availablePlugins = QPlatformIntegrationFactory::keys(platformPluginPath);
1202 for (const auto &pluginArgument : plugins) {
1203 // Split into platform name and arguments
1204 QStringList arguments = pluginArgument.split(sep: u':', behavior: Qt::SkipEmptyParts);
1205 if (arguments.isEmpty())
1206 continue;
1207 const QString name = arguments.takeFirst().toLower();
1208 QString argumentsKey = name;
1209 if (name.isEmpty())
1210 continue;
1211 argumentsKey[0] = argumentsKey.at(i: 0).toUpper();
1212 arguments.append(l: QLibraryInfo::platformPluginArguments(platformName: argumentsKey));
1213
1214 qCDebug(lcQpaPluginLoading) << "Attempting to load Qt platform plugin" << name << "with arguments" << arguments;
1215
1216 // Create the platform integration.
1217 QGuiApplicationPrivate::platform_integration = QPlatformIntegrationFactory::create(name, args: arguments, argc, argv, platformPluginPath);
1218 if (Q_UNLIKELY(!QGuiApplicationPrivate::platform_integration)) {
1219 if (availablePlugins.contains(str: name)) {
1220 qCInfo(lcQpaPluginLoading).nospace().noquote()
1221 << "Could not load the Qt platform plugin \"" << name << "\" in \""
1222 << QDir::toNativeSeparators(pathName: platformPluginPath) << "\" even though it was found.";
1223 } else {
1224 qCWarning(lcQpaPluginLoading).nospace().noquote()
1225 << "Could not find the Qt platform plugin \"" << name << "\" in \""
1226 << QDir::toNativeSeparators(pathName: platformPluginPath) << "\"";
1227 }
1228 } else {
1229 qCDebug(lcQpaPluginLoading) << "Successfully loaded Qt platform plugin" << name;
1230 QGuiApplicationPrivate::platform_name = new QString(name);
1231 platformArguments = arguments;
1232 break;
1233 }
1234 }
1235
1236 if (Q_UNLIKELY(!QGuiApplicationPrivate::platform_integration)) {
1237 QString fatalMessage = QStringLiteral("This application failed to start because no Qt platform plugin could be initialized. "
1238 "Reinstalling the application may fix this problem.\n");
1239
1240 if (!availablePlugins.isEmpty())
1241 fatalMessage += "\nAvailable platform plugins are: %1.\n"_L1.arg(args: availablePlugins.join(sep: ", "_L1));
1242
1243#if defined(Q_OS_WIN)
1244 // Windows: Display message box unless it is a console application
1245 // or debug build showing an assert box.
1246 if (!QLibraryInfo::isDebugBuild() && !GetConsoleWindow())
1247 MessageBox(0, (LPCTSTR)fatalMessage.utf16(), (LPCTSTR)(QCoreApplication::applicationName().utf16()), MB_OK | MB_ICONERROR);
1248#endif // Q_OS_WIN
1249 qFatal(msg: "%s", qPrintable(fatalMessage));
1250
1251 return;
1252 }
1253
1254 // Create the platform theme:
1255
1256 // 1) Fetch the platform name from the environment if present.
1257 QStringList themeNames;
1258 if (!platformThemeName.isEmpty()) {
1259 qCDebug(lcQpaTheme) << "Adding" << platformThemeName << "from environment to list of theme names";
1260 themeNames.append(t: platformThemeName);
1261 }
1262
1263 // 2) Special case - check whether it's a flatpak or snap app to use xdg-desktop-portal platform theme for portals support
1264 if (checkNeedPortalSupport()) {
1265 qCDebug(lcQpaTheme) << "Adding xdgdesktopportal to list of theme names";
1266 themeNames.append(QStringLiteral("xdgdesktopportal"));
1267 }
1268
1269 // 3) Ask the platform integration for a list of theme names
1270 const auto platformIntegrationThemeNames = QGuiApplicationPrivate::platform_integration->themeNames();
1271 qCDebug(lcQpaTheme) << "Adding platform integration's theme names to list of theme names:" << platformIntegrationThemeNames;
1272 themeNames += platformIntegrationThemeNames;
1273 // 4) Look for a theme plugin.
1274 for (const QString &themeName : std::as_const(t&: themeNames)) {
1275 qCDebug(lcQpaTheme) << "Attempting to create platform theme" << themeName << "via QPlatformThemeFactory::create";
1276 QGuiApplicationPrivate::platform_theme = QPlatformThemeFactory::create(key: themeName, platformPluginPath);
1277 if (QGuiApplicationPrivate::platform_theme) {
1278 qCDebug(lcQpaTheme) << "Successfully created platform theme" << themeName;
1279 break;
1280 }
1281 }
1282
1283 // 5) If no theme plugin was found ask the platform integration to
1284 // create a theme
1285 if (!QGuiApplicationPrivate::platform_theme) {
1286 for (const QString &themeName : std::as_const(t&: themeNames)) {
1287 qCDebug(lcQpaTheme) << "Attempting to create platform theme" << themeName << "via createPlatformTheme";
1288 QGuiApplicationPrivate::platform_theme = QGuiApplicationPrivate::platform_integration->createPlatformTheme(name: themeName);
1289 if (QGuiApplicationPrivate::platform_theme) {
1290 qCDebug(lcQpaTheme) << "Successfully created platform theme" << themeName;
1291 break;
1292 }
1293 }
1294 // No error message; not having a theme plugin is allowed.
1295 }
1296
1297 // 6) Fall back on the built-in "null" platform theme.
1298 if (!QGuiApplicationPrivate::platform_theme) {
1299 qCDebug(lcQpaTheme) << "Failed to create platform theme; using \"null\" platform theme";
1300 QGuiApplicationPrivate::platform_theme = new QPlatformTheme;
1301 }
1302
1303 // Set arguments as dynamic properties on the native interface as
1304 // boolean 'foo' or strings: 'foo=bar'
1305 if (!platformArguments.isEmpty()) {
1306 if (QObject *nativeInterface = QGuiApplicationPrivate::platform_integration->nativeInterface()) {
1307 for (const QString &argument : std::as_const(t&: platformArguments)) {
1308 const int equalsPos = argument.indexOf(c: u'=');
1309 const QByteArray name =
1310 equalsPos != -1 ? argument.left(n: equalsPos).toUtf8() : argument.toUtf8();
1311 const QVariant value =
1312 equalsPos != -1 ? QVariant(argument.mid(position: equalsPos + 1)) : QVariant(true);
1313 nativeInterface->setProperty(name: name.constData(), value);
1314 }
1315 }
1316 }
1317
1318 const auto platformIntegration = QGuiApplicationPrivate::platformIntegration();
1319 fontSmoothingGamma = platformIntegration->styleHint(hint: QPlatformIntegration::FontSmoothingGamma).toReal();
1320 QCoreApplication::setAttribute(attribute: Qt::AA_DontShowShortcutsInContextMenus,
1321 on: !platformIntegration->styleHint(hint: QPlatformIntegration::ShowShortcutsInContextMenus).toBool());
1322}
1323
1324static void init_plugins(const QList<QByteArray> &pluginList)
1325{
1326 for (int i = 0; i < pluginList.size(); ++i) {
1327 QByteArray pluginSpec = pluginList.at(i);
1328 int colonPos = pluginSpec.indexOf(c: ':');
1329 QObject *plugin;
1330 if (colonPos < 0)
1331 plugin = QGenericPluginFactory::create(QLatin1StringView(pluginSpec), QString());
1332 else
1333 plugin = QGenericPluginFactory::create(QLatin1StringView(pluginSpec.mid(index: 0, len: colonPos)),
1334 QLatin1StringView(pluginSpec.mid(index: colonPos+1)));
1335 if (plugin)
1336 QGuiApplicationPrivate::generic_plugin_list.append(t: plugin);
1337 else
1338 qWarning(msg: "No such plugin for spec \"%s\"", pluginSpec.constData());
1339 }
1340}

1342#if QT_CONFIG(commandlineparser)
1343void QGuiApplicationPrivate::addQtOptions(QList<QCommandLineOption> *options)
1344{
1345 QCoreApplicationPrivate::addQtOptions(options);
1346
1347#if defined(Q_OS_UNIX) && !defined(Q_OS_DARWIN)
1348 const QByteArray sessionType = qgetenv(varName: "XDG_SESSION_TYPE");
1349 const bool x11 = sessionType == "x11";
1350 // Technically the x11 aliases are only available if platformName is "xcb", but we can't know that here.
1351#else
1352 const bool x11 = false;
1353#endif
1354
1355 options->append(t: QCommandLineOption(QStringLiteral("platform"),

1396void QGuiApplicationPrivate::createPlatformIntegration()
1397{
1398 QHighDpiScaling::initHighDpiScaling();
1399
1400 // Load the platform integration
1401 QString platformPluginPath = QString::fromLocal8Bit(ba: qgetenv(varName: "QT_QPA_PLATFORM_PLUGIN_PATH"));
1402
1403
1404 QByteArray platformName;
1405#ifdef QT_QPA_DEFAULT_PLATFORM_NAME
1406 platformName = QT_QPA_DEFAULT_PLATFORM_NAME;
1407#endif
1408#if defined(Q_OS_UNIX) && !defined(Q_OS_DARWIN)
1409 QList<QByteArray> platformArguments = platformName.split(sep: ':');
1410 QByteArray platformPluginBase = platformArguments.first();
1411
1412 const bool hasWaylandDisplay = qEnvironmentVariableIsSet(varName: "WAYLAND_DISPLAY");
1413 const bool isWaylandSessionType = qgetenv(varName: "XDG_SESSION_TYPE") == "wayland";
1414
1415 QVector<QByteArray> preferredPlatformOrder;
1416 const bool defaultIsXcb = platformPluginBase == "xcb";
1417 const QByteArray xcbPlatformName = defaultIsXcb ? platformName : "xcb";
1418 if (qEnvironmentVariableIsSet(varName: "DISPLAY")) {
1419 preferredPlatformOrder << xcbPlatformName;
1420 if (defaultIsXcb)
1421 platformName.clear();
1422 }
1423
1424 const bool defaultIsWayland = !defaultIsXcb && platformPluginBase.startsWith(bv: "wayland");
1425 const QByteArray waylandPlatformName = defaultIsWayland ? platformName : "wayland";
1426 if (hasWaylandDisplay || isWaylandSessionType) {
1427 preferredPlatformOrder.prepend(t: waylandPlatformName);
1428
1429 if (defaultIsWayland)
1430 platformName.clear();
1431 }
1432
1433 if (!platformName.isEmpty())
1434 preferredPlatformOrder.append(t: platformName);
1435
1436 platformName = preferredPlatformOrder.join(sep: ';');
1437#endif
1438
1439 bool platformExplicitlySelected = false;
1440 QByteArray platformNameEnv = qgetenv(varName: "QT_QPA_PLATFORM");
1441 if (!platformNameEnv.isEmpty()) {
1442 platformName = platformNameEnv;
1443 platformExplicitlySelected = true;
1444 }
1445
1446 QString platformThemeName = QString::fromLocal8Bit(ba: qgetenv(varName: "QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME"));
1447
1448 // Get command line params
1449
1450 QString icon;
1451
1452 int j = argc ? 1 : 0;
1453 for (int i=1; i<argc; i++) {
1454 if (!argv[i])
1455 continue;
1456 if (*argv[i] != '-') {
1457 argv[j++] = argv[i];
1458 continue;
1459 }
1460 const bool xcbIsDefault = platformName.startsWith(bv: "xcb");
1461 const char *arg = argv[i];
1462 if (arg[1] == '-') // startsWith("--")
1463 ++arg;
1464 if (strcmp(s1: arg, s2: "-platformpluginpath") == 0) {
1465 if (++i < argc)
1466 platformPluginPath = QFile::decodeName(localFileName: argv[i]);
1467 } else if (strcmp(s1: arg, s2: "-platform") == 0) {
1468 if (++i < argc) {
1469 platformExplicitlySelected = true;
1470 platformName = argv[i];
1471 }
1472 } else if (strcmp(s1: arg, s2: "-platformtheme") == 0) {
1473 if (++i < argc)
1474 platformThemeName = QString::fromLocal8Bit(ba: argv[i]);
1475 } else if (strcmp(s1: arg, s2: "-qwindowgeometry") == 0 || (xcbIsDefault && strcmp(s1: arg, s2: "-geometry") == 0)) {
1476 if (++i < argc)
1477 windowGeometrySpecification = QWindowGeometrySpecification::fromArgument(a: argv[i]);
1478 } else if (strcmp(s1: arg, s2: "-qwindowtitle") == 0 || (xcbIsDefault && strcmp(s1: arg, s2: "-title") == 0)) {
1479 if (++i < argc)
1480 firstWindowTitle = QString::fromLocal8Bit(ba: argv[i]);
1481 } else if (strcmp(s1: arg, s2: "-qwindowicon") == 0 || (xcbIsDefault && strcmp(s1: arg, s2: "-icon") == 0)) {
1482 if (++i < argc) {
1483 icon = QFile::decodeName(localFileName: argv[i]);
1484 }
1485 } else {
1486 argv[j++] = argv[i];
1487 }
1488 }
1489
1490 if (j < argc) {
1491 argv[j] = nullptr;
1492 argc = j;
1493 }
1494
1495 Q_UNUSED(platformExplicitlySelected);
1496
1497 init_platform(pluginNamesWithArguments: QLatin1StringView(platformName), platformPluginPath, platformThemeName, argc, argv);
1498 if (const QPlatformTheme *theme = platformTheme())
1499 QStyleHintsPrivate::get(q: QGuiApplication::styleHints())->setColorScheme(theme->colorScheme());
1500
1501 if (!icon.isEmpty())
1502 forcedWindowIcon = QDir::isAbsolutePath(path: icon) ? QIcon(icon) : QIcon::fromTheme(name: icon);
1503}

1532void Q_TRACE_INSTRUMENT(qtgui) QGuiApplicationPrivate::init()
1533{
1534 Q_TRACE_SCOPE(QGuiApplicationPrivate_init);
1535
1536#if defined(Q_OS_MACOS)
1537 QMacAutoReleasePool pool;
1538#endif
1539
1540 QCoreApplicationPrivate::init();
1541
1542 QCoreApplicationPrivate::is_app_running = false; // Starting up.
1543
1544 bool loadTestability = false;
1545 QList<QByteArray> pluginList;
1546 // Get command line params
1547#ifndef QT_NO_SESSIONMANAGER
1548 QString session_id;
1549 QString session_key;
1550# if defined(Q_OS_WIN)
1551 wchar_t guidstr[40];
1552 GUID guid;
1553 CoCreateGuid(&guid);
1554 StringFromGUID2(guid, guidstr, 40);
1555 session_id = QString::fromWCharArray(guidstr);
1556 CoCreateGuid(&guid);
1557 StringFromGUID2(guid, guidstr, 40);
1558 session_key = QString::fromWCharArray(guidstr);
1559# endif
1560#endif
1561 QString s;
1562 int j = argc ? 1 : 0;
1563 for (int i=1; i<argc; i++) {
1564 if (!argv[i])
1565 continue;
1566 if (*argv[i] != '-') {
1567 argv[j++] = argv[i];
1568 continue;
1569 }
1570 const char *arg = argv[i];
1571 if (arg[1] == '-') // startsWith("--")
1572 ++arg;
1573 if (strcmp(s1: arg, s2: "-plugin") == 0) {

1576 } else if (strcmp(s1: arg, s2: "-reverse") == 0) {

1578#ifdef Q_OS_MAC

1584 QString qbundlePath = QCFString(CFURLCopyFileSystemPath(bundleURL,

1588 }
1589#endif
1590#ifndef QT_NO_SESSIONMANAGER
1591 } else if (strcmp(s1: arg, s2: "-session") == 0 && i < argc - 1) {
1592 ++i;
1593 if (argv[i] && *argv[i]) {
1594 session_id = QString::fromLatin1(ba: argv[i]);
1595 int p = session_id.indexOf(c: u'_');
1596 if (p >= 0) {
1597 session_key = session_id.mid(position: p +1);
1598 session_id = session_id.left(n: p);
1599 }
1600 is_session_restored = true;
1601 }
1602#endif
1603 } else if (strcmp(s1: arg, s2: "-testability") == 0) {
1604 loadTestability = true;
1605 } else if (strncmp(s1: arg, s2: "-style=", n: 7) == 0) {
1606 s = QString::fromLocal8Bit(ba: arg + 7);
1607 } else if (strcmp(s1: arg, s2: "-style") == 0 && i < argc - 1) {
1608 s = QString::fromLocal8Bit(ba: argv[++i]);
1609 } else {
1610 argv[j++] = argv[i];
1611 }
1612
1613 if (!s.isEmpty())
1614 styleOverride = s;
1615 }
1616
1617 if (j < argc) {
1618 argv[j] = nullptr;
1619 argc = j;
1620 }
1621
1622 // Load environment exported generic plugins
1623 QByteArray envPlugins = qgetenv(varName: "QT_QPA_GENERIC_PLUGINS");
1624 if (!envPlugins.isEmpty())
1625 pluginList += envPlugins.split(sep: ',');
1626
1627 if (platform_integration == nullptr)
1628 createPlatformIntegration();
1629
1630 updatePalette();
1631 QFont::initialize();
1632 initThemeHints();
1633
1634#ifndef QT_NO_CURSOR
1635 QCursorData::initialize();
1636#endif
1637

1639 qRegisterGuiVariant();
1640

1644#endif

1647#ifndef QT_NO_OPENGL

1649 QOpenGLContext *ctx = new QOpenGLContext;

1653 ownGlobalShareContext = true;
1654 }
1655#endif
1656

1664#ifndef QT_NO_SESSIONMANAGER

1667#endif
1668
1669#if QT_CONFIG(library)
1670 if (qEnvironmentVariableIntValue(varName: "QT_LOAD_TESTABILITY") > 0)
1671 loadTestability = true;
1672

1674 QLibrary testLib(QStringLiteral("qttestability"));
1675 if (Q_UNLIKELY(!testLib.load())) {
1676 qCritical() << "Library qttestability load failed:" << testLib.errorString();
1677 } else {
1678 typedef void (*TasInitialize)(void);
1679 TasInitialize initFunction = (TasInitialize)testLib.resolve(symbol: "qt_testability_init");
1680 if (Q_UNLIKELY(!initFunction)) {
1681 qCritical(msg: "Library qttestability resolve failed!");
1682 } else {

1687#else

1689#endif // QT_CONFIG(library)

1691 // trigger changed signal and event delivery

1860 returns the value that was set to exit() (which is 0 if exit() is called

1863 It is necessary to call this function to start event handling. The main
1864 event loop receives events from the window system and dispatches these to
1865 the application widgets.
1866
1867 Generally, no user interaction can take place before calling exec().
1868
1869 To make your application perform idle processing, e.g., executing a special
1870 function whenever there are no pending events, use a QTimer with 0 timeout.
1871 More advanced idle processing schemes can be achieved using processEvents().
1872
1873 We recommend that you connect clean-up code to the
1874 \l{QCoreApplication::}{aboutToQuit()} signal, instead of putting it in your
1875 application's \c{main()} function. This is because, on some platforms, the
1876 QApplication::exec() call may not return.

1878 \sa quitOnLastWindowClosed, quit(), exit(), processEvents(),
1879 QCoreApplication::exec()
1880*/

1888
1889void QGuiApplicationPrivate::captureGlobalModifierState(QEvent *e)
1890{
1891 if (e->spontaneous()) {
1892 // Capture the current mouse and keyboard states. Doing so here is
1893 // required in order to support Qt Test synthesized events. Real mouse
1894 // and keyboard state updates from the platform plugin are managed by
1895 // QGuiApplicationPrivate::process(Mouse|Wheel|Key|Touch|Tablet)Event();
1896 // ### FIXME: Qt Test should not call qapp->notify(), but rather route
1897 // the events through the proper QPA interface. This is required to
1898 // properly generate all other events such as enter/leave etc.
1899 switch (e->type()) {
1900 case QEvent::MouseButtonPress: {
1901 QMouseEvent *me = static_cast<QMouseEvent *>(e);
1902 QGuiApplicationPrivate::modifier_buttons = me->modifiers();
1903 QGuiApplicationPrivate::mouse_buttons |= me->button();
1904 break;
1905 }
1906 case QEvent::MouseButtonDblClick: {
1907 QMouseEvent *me = static_cast<QMouseEvent *>(e);
1908 QGuiApplicationPrivate::modifier_buttons = me->modifiers();
1909 QGuiApplicationPrivate::mouse_buttons |= me->button();
1910 break;
1911 }
1912 case QEvent::MouseButtonRelease: {
1913 QMouseEvent *me = static_cast<QMouseEvent *>(e);
1914 QGuiApplicationPrivate::modifier_buttons = me->modifiers();
1915 QGuiApplicationPrivate::mouse_buttons &= ~me->button();
1916 break;
1917 }
1918 case QEvent::KeyPress:
1919 case QEvent::KeyRelease:
1920 case QEvent::MouseMove:
1921#if QT_CONFIG(wheelevent)
1922 case QEvent::Wheel:
1923#endif
1924 case QEvent::TouchBegin:
1925 case QEvent::TouchUpdate:
1926 case QEvent::TouchEnd:
1927#if QT_CONFIG(tabletevent)
1928 case QEvent::TabletMove:
1929 case QEvent::TabletPress:
1930 case QEvent::TabletRelease:
1931#endif
1932 {
1933 QInputEvent *ie = static_cast<QInputEvent *>(e);
1934 QGuiApplicationPrivate::modifier_buttons = ie->modifiers();
1935 break;
1936 }
1937 default:
1938 break;
1939 }
1940 }
1941}

1943/*! \reimp
1944*/
1945bool QGuiApplication::notify(QObject *object, QEvent *event)
1946{
1947 if (object->isWindowType()) {
1948 if (QGuiApplicationPrivate::sendQWindowEventToQPlatformWindow(window: static_cast<QWindow *>(object), event))
1949 return true; // Platform plugin ate the event
1950 }
1951
1952 QGuiApplicationPrivate::captureGlobalModifierState(e: event);
1953
1954 return QCoreApplication::notify(object, event);
1955}
1956
1957/*! \reimp
1958*/
1959bool QGuiApplication::event(QEvent *e)
1960{
1961 if (e->type() == QEvent::LanguageChange) {
1962 // if the layout direction was set explicitly, then don't override it here
1963 if (layout_direction == Qt::LayoutDirectionAuto)
1964 setLayoutDirection(layout_direction);
1965 for (auto *topLevelWindow : QGuiApplication::topLevelWindows()) {
1966 if (topLevelWindow->flags() != Qt::Desktop)
1967 postEvent(receiver: topLevelWindow, event: new QEvent(QEvent::LanguageChange));
1968 }
1969 } else if (e->type() == QEvent::ApplicationFontChange ||
1970 e->type() == QEvent::ApplicationPaletteChange) {
1971 for (auto *topLevelWindow : QGuiApplication::topLevelWindows()) {
1972 if (topLevelWindow->flags() != Qt::Desktop)
1973 postEvent(receiver: topLevelWindow, event: new QEvent(e->type()));
1974 }
1975 } else if (e->type() == QEvent::Quit) {
1976 // Close open windows. This is done in order to deliver de-expose
1977 // events while the event loop is still running.
1978 for (QWindow *topLevelWindow : QGuiApplication::topLevelWindows()) {
1979 // Already closed windows will not have a platform window, skip those
1980 if (!topLevelWindow->handle())
1981 continue;
1982 if (!topLevelWindow->close()) {
1983 e->ignore();
1984 return true;
1985 }
1986 }
1987 }
1988
1989 return QCoreApplication::event(e);
1990}

1992/*!
1993 \internal
1994*/

2627void QGuiApplicationPrivate::processGeometryChangeEvent(QWindowSystemInterfacePrivate::GeometryChangeEvent *e)
2628{
2629 if (e->window.isNull())
2630 return;
2631
2632 QWindow *window = e->window.data();
2633 if (!window)
2634 return;
2635
2636 const QRect lastReportedGeometry = window->d_func()->geometry;
2637 const QRect requestedGeometry = e->requestedGeometry;
2638 const QRect actualGeometry = e->newGeometry;
2639
2640 // We send size and move events only if the geometry has changed from
2641 // what was last reported, or if the user tried to set a new geometry,
2642 // but the window manager responded by keeping the old geometry. In the
2643 // latter case we send move/resize events with the same geometry as the
2644 // last reported geometry, to indicate that the window wasn't moved or
2645 // resized. Note that this logic does not apply to the property changes
2646 // of the window, as we don't treat them as part of this request/response
2647 // protocol of QWindow/QPA.
2648 const bool isResize = actualGeometry.size() != lastReportedGeometry.size()
2649 || requestedGeometry.size() != actualGeometry.size();
2650 const bool isMove = actualGeometry.topLeft() != lastReportedGeometry.topLeft()
2651 || requestedGeometry.topLeft() != actualGeometry.topLeft();
2652
2653 window->d_func()->geometry = actualGeometry;
2654
2655 if (isResize || window->d_func()->resizeEventPending) {
2656 QResizeEvent e(actualGeometry.size(), lastReportedGeometry.size());
2657 QGuiApplication::sendSpontaneousEvent(receiver: window, event: &e);
2658
2659 window->d_func()->resizeEventPending = false;
2660
2661 if (actualGeometry.width() != lastReportedGeometry.width())
2662 emit window->widthChanged(arg: actualGeometry.width());
2663 if (actualGeometry.height() != lastReportedGeometry.height())
2664 emit window->heightChanged(arg: actualGeometry.height());
2665 }
2666
2667 if (isMove) {
2668 //### frame geometry
2669 QMoveEvent e(actualGeometry.topLeft(), lastReportedGeometry.topLeft());
2670 QGuiApplication::sendSpontaneousEvent(receiver: window, event: &e);
2671
2672 if (actualGeometry.x() != lastReportedGeometry.x())
2673 emit window->xChanged(arg: actualGeometry.x());
2674 if (actualGeometry.y() != lastReportedGeometry.y())
2675 emit window->yChanged(arg: actualGeometry.y());
2676 }
2677}

2747 pointData.target = nullptr;

2788 e->global, e->buttons, e->modifiers, button, mouseType, Qt::MouseEventNotSynthesized, false, device);

2868void QGuiApplicationPrivate::processTouchEvent(QWindowSystemInterfacePrivate::TouchEvent *e)
2869{
2870 if (!QInputDevicePrivate::isRegistered(dev: e->device))
2871 return;
2872
2873 modifier_buttons = e->modifiers;
2874 QPointingDevice *device = const_cast<QPointingDevice *>(static_cast<const QPointingDevice *>(e->device));
2875 QPointingDevicePrivate *devPriv = QPointingDevicePrivate::get(q: device);
2876
2877 if (e->touchType == QEvent::TouchCancel) {
2878 // The touch sequence has been canceled (e.g. by the compositor).
2879 // Send the TouchCancel to all windows with active touches and clean up.
2880 QTouchEvent touchEvent(QEvent::TouchCancel, device, e->modifiers);
2881 touchEvent.setTimestamp(e->timestamp);
2882 QSet<QWindow *> windowsNeedingCancel;
2883
2884 for (auto &epd : devPriv->activePoints.values()) {
2885 if (QWindow *w = QMutableEventPoint::window(p: epd.eventPoint))
2886 windowsNeedingCancel.insert(value: w);
2887 }
2888
2889 for (QSet<QWindow *>::const_iterator winIt = windowsNeedingCancel.constBegin(),
2890 winItEnd = windowsNeedingCancel.constEnd(); winIt != winItEnd; ++winIt) {
2891 QGuiApplication::sendSpontaneousEvent(receiver: *winIt, event: &touchEvent);
2892 }
2893 if (!self->synthesizedMousePoints.isEmpty() && !e->synthetic()) {
2894 for (QHash<QWindow *, SynthesizedMouseData>::const_iterator synthIt = self->synthesizedMousePoints.constBegin(),
2895 synthItEnd = self->synthesizedMousePoints.constEnd(); synthIt != synthItEnd; ++synthIt) {
2896 if (!synthIt->window)
2897 continue;
2898 QWindowSystemInterfacePrivate::MouseEvent fake(synthIt->window.data(),
2899 e->timestamp,
2900 synthIt->pos,
2901 synthIt->screenPos,
2902 Qt::NoButton,
2903 e->modifiers,
2904 Qt::LeftButton,
2905 QEvent::MouseButtonRelease,
2906 Qt::MouseEventNotSynthesized,
2907 false,
2908 device);
2909 fake.flags |= QWindowSystemInterfacePrivate::WindowSystemEvent::Synthetic;
2910 processMouseEvent(e: &fake);
2911 }
2912 self->synthesizedMousePoints.clear();
2913 }
2914 self->lastTouchType = e->touchType;
2915 return;
2916 }
2917
2918 // Prevent sending ill-formed event sequences: Cancel can only be followed by a Begin.
2919 if (self->lastTouchType == QEvent::TouchCancel && e->touchType != QEvent::TouchBegin)
2920 return;
2921
2922 self->lastTouchType = e->touchType;
2923
2924 QPointer<QWindow> window = e->window; // the platform hopefully tells us which window received the event
2925 QVarLengthArray<QMutableTouchEvent, 2> touchEvents;
2926
2927 // For each temporary QEventPoint from the QPA TouchEvent:
2928 // - update the persistent QEventPoint in QPointingDevicePrivate::activePoints with current values
2929 // - determine which window to deliver it to
2930 // - add it to the QTouchEvent instance for that window (QMutableTouchEvent::target() will be QWindow*, for now)
2931 for (auto &tempPt : e->points) {
2932 // update state
2933 auto epd = devPriv->pointById(id: tempPt.id());
2934 auto &ep = epd->eventPoint;
2935 epd->eventPoint.setAccepted(false);
2936 switch (tempPt.state()) {
2937 case QEventPoint::State::Pressed:
2938 // On touchpads, send all touch points to the same window.
2939 if (!window && e->device && e->device->type() == QInputDevice::DeviceType::TouchPad)
2940 window = devPriv->firstActiveWindow();
2941 // If the QPA event didn't tell us which window, find the one under the touchpoint position.
2942 if (!window)
2943 window = QGuiApplication::topLevelAt(pos: tempPt.globalPosition().toPoint());
2944 QMutableEventPoint::setWindow(p&: ep, arg: window);
2945 break;
2946
2947 case QEventPoint::State::Released:
2948 if (Q_UNLIKELY(!window.isNull() && window != QMutableEventPoint::window(ep)))
2949 qCDebug(lcPtrDispatch) << "delivering touch release to same window"
2950 << QMutableEventPoint::window(p: ep) << "not" << window.data();
2951 window = QMutableEventPoint::window(p: ep);
2952 break;
2953
2954 default: // update or stationary
2955 if (Q_UNLIKELY(!window.isNull() && window != QMutableEventPoint::window(ep)))
2956 qCDebug(lcPtrDispatch) << "delivering touch update to same window"
2957 << QMutableEventPoint::window(p: ep) << "not" << window.data();
2958 window = QMutableEventPoint::window(p: ep);
2959 break;
2960 }
2961 // If we somehow still don't have a window, we can't deliver this touchpoint. (should never happen)
2962 if (Q_UNLIKELY(!window)) {
2963 qCWarning(lcPtrDispatch) << "skipping" << &tempPt << ": no target window";
2964 continue;
2965 }
2966 QMutableEventPoint::update(from: tempPt, to&: ep);
2967
2968 Q_ASSERT(window.data() != nullptr);
2969
2970 // make the *scene* position the same as the *global* position
2971 QMutableEventPoint::setScenePosition(p&: ep, arg: tempPt.globalPosition());
2972
2973 // store the scene position as local position, for now
2974 QMutableEventPoint::setPosition(p&: ep, arg: window->mapFromGlobal(pos: tempPt.globalPosition()));
2975
2976 // setTimeStamp has side effects, so we do it last
2977 QMutableEventPoint::setTimestamp(p&: ep, t: e->timestamp);
2978
2979 // add the touchpoint to the event that will be delivered to the window
2980 bool added = false;
2981 for (QMutableTouchEvent &ev : touchEvents) {
2982 if (ev.target() == window.data()) {
2983 ev.addPoint(point: ep);
2984 added = true;
2985 break;
2986 }
2987 }
2988 if (!added) {
2989 QMutableTouchEvent mte(e->touchType, device, e->modifiers, {ep});
2990 mte.setTimestamp(e->timestamp);
2991 mte.setTarget(window.data());
2992 touchEvents.append(t: mte);
2993 }
2994 }
2995
2996 if (touchEvents.isEmpty())
2997 return;
2998
2999 for (QMutableTouchEvent &touchEvent : touchEvents) {
3000 QWindow *window = static_cast<QWindow *>(touchEvent.target());
3001
3002 QEvent::Type eventType;
3003 switch (touchEvent.touchPointStates()) {
3004 case QEventPoint::State::Pressed:
3005 eventType = QEvent::TouchBegin;
3006 break;
3007 case QEventPoint::State::Released:
3008 eventType = QEvent::TouchEnd;
3009 break;
3010 default:
3011 eventType = QEvent::TouchUpdate;
3012 break;
3013 }
3014
3015 if (window->d_func()->blockedByModalWindow && !qApp->d_func()->popupActive()) {
3016 // a modal window is blocking this window, don't allow touch events through
3017
3018 // QTBUG-37371 temporary fix; TODO: revisit when we have a forwarding solution
3019 if (touchEvent.type() == QEvent::TouchEnd) {
3020 // but don't leave dangling state: e.g.
3021 // QQuickWindowPrivate::itemForTouchPointId needs to be cleared.
3022 QTouchEvent touchEvent(QEvent::TouchCancel, device, e->modifiers);
3023 touchEvent.setTimestamp(e->timestamp);
3024 QGuiApplication::sendSpontaneousEvent(receiver: window, event: &touchEvent);
3025 }
3026 continue;
3027 }
3028
3029 // Note: after the call to sendSpontaneousEvent, touchEvent.position() will have
3030 // changed to reflect the local position inside the last (random) widget it tried
3031 // to deliver the touch event to, and will therefore be invalid afterwards.
3032 QGuiApplication::sendSpontaneousEvent(receiver: window, event: &touchEvent);
3033
3034 if (!e->synthetic() && !touchEvent.isAccepted() && qApp->testAttribute(attribute: Qt::AA_SynthesizeMouseForUnhandledTouchEvents)) {
3035 // exclude devices which generate their own mouse events
3036 if (!(touchEvent.device()->capabilities().testFlag(flag: QInputDevice::Capability::MouseEmulation))) {
3037
3038 QEvent::Type mouseEventType = QEvent::MouseMove;
3039 Qt::MouseButton button = Qt::NoButton;
3040 Qt::MouseButtons buttons = Qt::LeftButton;
3041 if (eventType == QEvent::TouchBegin || m_fakeMouseSourcePointId < 0) {
3042 m_fakeMouseSourcePointId = touchEvent.point(i: 0).id();
3043 qCDebug(lcPtrDispatch) << "synthesizing mouse events from touchpoint" << m_fakeMouseSourcePointId;
3044 }
3045 if (m_fakeMouseSourcePointId >= 0) {
3046 const auto *touchPoint = touchEvent.pointById(id: m_fakeMouseSourcePointId);
3047 if (touchPoint) {
3048 switch (touchPoint->state()) {
3049 case QEventPoint::State::Pressed:
3050 mouseEventType = QEvent::MouseButtonPress;
3051 button = Qt::LeftButton;
3052 break;
3053 case QEventPoint::State::Released:
3054 mouseEventType = QEvent::MouseButtonRelease;
3055 button = Qt::LeftButton;
3056 buttons = Qt::NoButton;
3057 Q_ASSERT(m_fakeMouseSourcePointId == touchPoint->id());
3058 m_fakeMouseSourcePointId = -1;
3059 break;
3060 default:
3061 break;
3062 }
3063 if (touchPoint->state() != QEventPoint::State::Released) {
3064 self->synthesizedMousePoints.insert(key: window, value: SynthesizedMouseData(
3065 touchPoint->position(), touchPoint->globalPosition(), window));
3066 }
3067 // All touch events that are not accepted by the application will be translated to
3068 // left mouse button events instead (see AA_SynthesizeMouseForUnhandledTouchEvents docs).
3069 // TODO why go through QPA? Why not just send a QMouseEvent right from here?
3070 QWindowSystemInterfacePrivate::MouseEvent fake(window, e->timestamp,
3071 window->mapFromGlobal(pos: touchPoint->globalPosition().toPoint()),
3072 touchPoint->globalPosition(),
3073 buttons,
3074 e->modifiers,
3075 button,
3076 mouseEventType,
3077 Qt::MouseEventSynthesizedByQt,
3078 false,
3079 device);
3080 fake.flags |= QWindowSystemInterfacePrivate::WindowSystemEvent::Synthetic;
3081 processMouseEvent(e: &fake);
3082 }
3083 }
3084 if (eventType == QEvent::TouchEnd)
3085 self->synthesizedMousePoints.clear();
3086 }
3087 }
3088 }
3089
3090 // Remove released points from QPointingDevicePrivate::activePoints only after the event is
3091 // delivered. Widgets and Qt Quick are allowed to access them at any time before this.
3092 for (const QEventPoint &touchPoint : e->points) {
3093 if (touchPoint.state() == QEventPoint::State::Released)
3094 devPriv->removePointById(id: touchPoint.id());
3095 }
3096}

3116void QGuiApplicationPrivate::processScreenGeometryChange(QWindowSystemInterfacePrivate::ScreenGeometryEvent *e)
3117{
3118 // This operation only makes sense after the QGuiApplication constructor runs
3119 if (QCoreApplication::startingUp())

3127 QScreenPrivate::UpdateEmitter updateEmitter(s);

3181void QGuiApplicationPrivate::processExposeEvent(QWindowSystemInterfacePrivate::ExposeEvent *e)
3182{
3183 if (!e->window)
3184 return;
3185
3186 QWindow *window = e->window.data();
3187 if (!window)
3188 return;
3189 QWindowPrivate *p = qt_window_private(window);
3190
3191 if (!p->receivedExpose) {
3192 if (p->resizeEventPending) {
3193 // as a convenience for plugins, send a resize event before the first expose event if they haven't done so
3194 // window->geometry() should have a valid size as soon as a handle exists.
3195 QResizeEvent e(window->geometry().size(), p->geometry.size());
3196 QGuiApplication::sendSpontaneousEvent(receiver: window, event: &e);
3197
3198 p->resizeEventPending = false;
3199 }
3200
3201 // FIXME: It would logically make sense to set this _after_ we've sent the
3202 // expose event to the window, to mark that it now has received an expose.
3203 // But some parts of Qt (mis)use this private member to check whether the
3204 // window has been mapped yet, which they do in code that is triggered
3205 // by the very same expose event we send below. To keep the code working
3206 // we need to set the variable up front, until the code has been fixed.
3207 p->receivedExpose = true;
3208 }
3209
3210 // If the platform does not send paint events we need to synthesize them from expose events
3211 const bool shouldSynthesizePaintEvents = !platformIntegration()->hasCapability(cap: QPlatformIntegration::PaintEvents);
3212
3213 const bool wasExposed = p->exposed;
3214 p->exposed = e->isExposed && window->screen();
3215
3216 // We treat expose events for an already exposed window as paint events
3217 if (wasExposed && p->exposed && shouldSynthesizePaintEvents) {
3218 QPaintEvent paintEvent(e->region);
3219 QCoreApplication::sendSpontaneousEvent(receiver: window, event: &paintEvent);
3220 if (paintEvent.isAccepted())
3221 return; // No need to send expose
3222
3223 // The paint event was not accepted, so we fall through and send an expose
3224 // event instead, to maintain compatibility for clients that haven't adopted
3225 // paint events yet.
3226 }
3227
3228 QExposeEvent exposeEvent(e->region);
3229 QCoreApplication::sendSpontaneousEvent(receiver: window, event: &exposeEvent);
3230 e->eventAccepted = exposeEvent.isAccepted();
3231
3232 // If the window was just exposed we also need to send a paint event,
3233 // so that clients that implement paint events will draw something.
3234 // Note that we we can not skip this based on the expose event being
3235 // accepted, as clients may implement exposeEvent to track the state
3236 // change, but without drawing anything.
3237 if (!wasExposed && p->exposed && shouldSynthesizePaintEvents) {
3238 QPaintEvent paintEvent(e->region);
3239 QCoreApplication::sendSpontaneousEvent(receiver: window, event: &paintEvent);
3240 }
3241}
3242
3243void QGuiApplicationPrivate::processPaintEvent(QWindowSystemInterfacePrivate::PaintEvent *e)
3244{
3245 Q_ASSERT_X(platformIntegration()->hasCapability(QPlatformIntegration::PaintEvents), "QGuiApplication",
3246 "The platform sent paint events without claiming support for it in QPlatformIntegration::capabilities()");
3247
3248 if (!e->window)
3249 return;
3250
3251 QPaintEvent paintEvent(e->region);
3252 QCoreApplication::sendSpontaneousEvent(receiver: e->window, event: &paintEvent);
3253
3254 // We report back the accepted state to the platform, so that it can
3255 // decide when the best time to send the fallback expose event is.
3256 e->eventAccepted = paintEvent.isAccepted();
3257}

3807 \fn void QGuiApplication::saveStateRequest(QSessionManager &manager)
3808
3809 This signal deals with \l{Session Management}{session management}. It is
3810 invoked when the \l{QSessionManager}{session manager} wants the application
3811 to preserve its state for a future session.
3812
3813 For example, a text editor would create a temporary file that includes the

3940 QGuiApplicationPrivate::platform_integration->sync();

3942 QWindowSystemInterface::flushWindowSystemEvents();

3946/*!
3947 \property QGuiApplication::layoutDirection
3948 \brief the default layout direction for this application
3949
3950 On system start-up, or when the direction is explicitly set to
3951 Qt::LayoutDirectionAuto, the default layout direction depends on the
3952 application's language.
3953
3954 The notifier signal was introduced in Qt 5.4.
3955
3956 \sa QWidget::layoutDirection, isLeftToRight(), isRightToLeft()
3957 */
3958
3959void QGuiApplication::setLayoutDirection(Qt::LayoutDirection direction)
3960{
3961 layout_direction = direction;
3962 if (direction == Qt::LayoutDirectionAuto)
3963 direction = qt_detectRTLLanguage() ? Qt::RightToLeft : Qt::LeftToRight;
3964
3965 // no change to the explicitly set or auto-detected layout direction
3966 if (direction == effective_layout_direction)
3967 return;
3968
3969 effective_layout_direction = direction;
3970 if (qGuiApp) {
3971 emit qGuiApp->layoutDirectionChanged(direction);
3972 QGuiApplicationPrivate::self->notifyLayoutDirectionChange();
3973 }
3974}
3975
3976Qt::LayoutDirection QGuiApplication::layoutDirection()
3977{
3978 /*
3979 effective_layout_direction defaults to Qt::LeftToRight, and is updated with what is
3980 auto-detected by a call to setLayoutDirection(Qt::LayoutDirectionAuto). This happens in
3981 QGuiApplicationPrivate::init and when the language changes (or before if the application
3982 calls the static function, but then no translators are installed so the auto-detection
3983 always yields Qt::LeftToRight).
3984 So we can be certain that it's always the right value.
3985 */
3986 return effective_layout_direction;
3987}

4026static inline void applyCursor(QWindow *w, QCursor c)
4027{
4028 if (const QScreen *screen = w->screen())
4029 if (QPlatformCursor *cursor = screen->handle()->cursor())
4030 cursor->changeCursor(windowCursor: &c, window: w);
4031}
4032
4033static inline void unsetCursor(QWindow *w)
4034{
4035 if (const QScreen *screen = w->screen())
4036 if (QPlatformCursor *cursor = screen->handle()->cursor())
4037 cursor->changeCursor(windowCursor: nullptr, window: w);
4038}
4039
4040static inline void applyCursor(const QList<QWindow *> &l, const QCursor &c)
4041{
4042 for (int i = 0; i < l.size(); ++i) {
4043 QWindow *w = l.at(i);
4044 if (w->handle() && w->type() != Qt::Desktop)
4045 applyCursor(w, c);
4046 }
4047}
4048
4049static inline void applyOverrideCursor(const QList<QScreen *> &screens, const QCursor &c)
4050{
4051 for (QScreen *screen : screens) {
4052 if (QPlatformCursor *cursor = screen->handle()->cursor())
4053 cursor->setOverrideCursor(c);
4054 }
4055}
4056
4057static inline void clearOverrideCursor(const QList<QScreen *> &screens)
4058{
4059 for (QScreen *screen : screens) {
4060 if (QPlatformCursor *cursor = screen->handle()->cursor())
4061 cursor->clearOverrideCursor();
4062 }
4063}
4064
4065static inline void applyWindowCursor(const QList<QWindow *> &l)
4066{
4067 for (int i = 0; i < l.size(); ++i) {
4068 QWindow *w = l.at(i);
4069 if (w->handle() && w->type() != Qt::Desktop) {
4070 if (qt_window_private(window: w)->hasCursor) {
4071 applyCursor(w, c: w->cursor());
4072 } else {
4073 unsetCursor(w);
4074 }
4075 }
4076 }

4079/*!
4080 \fn void QGuiApplication::setOverrideCursor(const QCursor &cursor)
4081
4082 Sets the application override cursor to \a cursor.
4083
4084 Application override cursors are intended for showing the user that the
4085 application is in a special state, for example during an operation that
4086 might take some time.
4087
4088 This cursor will be displayed in all the application's widgets until
4089 restoreOverrideCursor() or another setOverrideCursor() is called.
4090
4091 Application cursors are stored on an internal stack. setOverrideCursor()
4092 pushes the cursor onto the stack, and restoreOverrideCursor() pops the
4093 active cursor off the stack. changeOverrideCursor() changes the currently
4094 active application override cursor.
4095
4096 Every setOverrideCursor() must eventually be followed by a corresponding
4097 restoreOverrideCursor(), otherwise the stack will never be emptied.
4098
4099 Example:
4100 \snippet code/src_gui_kernel_qguiapplication_x11.cpp 0
4101
4102 \sa overrideCursor(), restoreOverrideCursor(), changeOverrideCursor(),
4103 QWidget::setCursor()
4104*/
4105void QGuiApplication::setOverrideCursor(const QCursor &cursor)
4106{
4107 CHECK_QAPP_INSTANCE()
4108 qGuiApp->d_func()->cursor_list.prepend(t: cursor);
4109 if (QPlatformCursor::capabilities().testFlag(flag: QPlatformCursor::OverrideCursor))
4110 applyOverrideCursor(screens: QGuiApplicationPrivate::screen_list, c: cursor);
4111 else
4112 applyCursor(l: QGuiApplicationPrivate::window_list, c: cursor);
4113}
4114
4115/*!
4116 \fn void QGuiApplication::restoreOverrideCursor()
4117
4118 Undoes the last setOverrideCursor().
4119
4120 If setOverrideCursor() has been called twice, calling
4121 restoreOverrideCursor() will activate the first cursor set. Calling this
4122 function a second time restores the original widgets' cursors.
4123
4124 \sa setOverrideCursor(), overrideCursor()
4125*/
4126void QGuiApplication::restoreOverrideCursor()
4127{
4128 CHECK_QAPP_INSTANCE()
4129 if (qGuiApp->d_func()->cursor_list.isEmpty())
4130 return;
4131 qGuiApp->d_func()->cursor_list.removeFirst();
4132 if (qGuiApp->d_func()->cursor_list.size() > 0) {
4133 QCursor c(qGuiApp->d_func()->cursor_list.value(i: 0));
4134 if (QPlatformCursor::capabilities().testFlag(flag: QPlatformCursor::OverrideCursor))
4135 applyOverrideCursor(screens: QGuiApplicationPrivate::screen_list, c);
4136 else
4137 applyCursor(l: QGuiApplicationPrivate::window_list, c);
4138 } else {
4139 if (QPlatformCursor::capabilities().testFlag(flag: QPlatformCursor::OverrideCursor))
4140 clearOverrideCursor(screens: QGuiApplicationPrivate::screen_list);
4141 applyWindowCursor(l: QGuiApplicationPrivate::window_list);
4142 }
4143}
4144#endif// QT_NO_CURSOR
